{
  "doc_id": "20189",
  "text": "A role for canonical initiation factors (eIFs) in mediating cellular IRES-dependent translation has also been proposed. Overexpression of eIF-4G and cleaved eIF-4G stimulate IRESmediated translation of ODC mRNA and Apaf-1 mRNA respectively [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The IRES elements of the cationic amino acid transporter protein 1 (Cat-1), c-myc and PDGF2 mRNAs function efficiently under conditions of amino acid starvation, genotoxic stress and cell differentiation, conditions which are associated with increased eIF-2α phosphorylation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
